# PiBun Desktop — Code Signing & Notarization
# Copy this to .env and fill in your credentials.
# See docs/CODE_SIGNING.md for full setup instructions.

# ── Code Signing (required) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your Apple Developer ID certificate identity.
# Find it with: security find-identity -v -p codesigning | grep "Developer ID"
ELECTROBUN_DEVELOPER_ID="Developer ID Application: Your Name (XXXXXXXXXX)"

# ── Notarization (choose one method) ────────────────────────────────────

# Method 1 — Apple ID (simpler, good for local builds)
# Generate an app-specific password at https://appleid.apple.com/account/manage
ELECTROBUN_APPLEID="your@apple.id"
ELECTROBUN_APPLEIDPASS="xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx"
ELECTROBUN_TEAMID="XXXXXXXXXX"

# Method 2 — App Store Connect API Key (recommended for CI)
# Create a key at https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/access/integrations/api
# ELECTROBUN_APPLEAPIISSUER="xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx"
# ELECTROBUN_APPLEAPIKEY="XXXXXXXXXX"
# ELECTROBUN_APPLEAPIKEYPATH="/path/to/AuthKey_XXXXXXXXXX.p8"
